<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_58"><name>Vehicle Interior</name><section id="_029927"><name>METER / GAUGE / DISPLAY</name><ttl id="_0137559"><name>METER / GAUGE SYSTEM</name><para id="RM100000000FSUV" category="J"><dtccode/><dtcname>Engine Coolant Temperature Gauge Malfunction</dtcname><subpara id="RM100000000FSUV_02" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The combination meter receives an engine coolant temperature signal from the ECM*1 engine coolant temperature sensor*2 or water temperature sender gauge assembly*3. The engine coolant temperature gauge needle position changes based on the resistance of the ECM*1 engine coolant temperature sensor*2 or water temperature sender gauge assembly*3.</ptxt><list1 type="nonmark"><item><ptxt>*1: for 1GR-FE</ptxt><ptxt>*2: for 1VD-FTV</ptxt><ptxt>*3: for 1HZ</ptxt></item></list1></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FSUV_03" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="E224935E14" width="7.168479331in" height="2.799876969in"/></figure><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="E300846E01" width="7.168479331in" height="2.799876969in"/></figure><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="E300846E02" width="7.168479331in" height="2.799876969in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FSUV_01" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM100000000FSUV_01_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK VEHICLE TYPE</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Check vehicle type.</ptxt></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.07in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.06in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Result</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>for 1GR-FE</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>A</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>for 1VD-FTV</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="3"><ptxt>B</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>for 1HZ</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>C</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM100000000FSUV_01_0011"/></result><result label="3" cellposition="1-4"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-4" childid="RM100000000FSUV_01_0015"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-7"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-7" childid="RM100000000FSUV_01_0002"/></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FSUV_01_0011" cellposition="2-1"><testtitle>CHECK COMBINATION METER ASSEMBLY</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Remove the combination meter assembly with the connector(s) still connected.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="E293693C03" width="3.434793307in" height="4.677165354in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="left"><ptxt>Component with harness connected</ptxt><ptxt>(Combination Meter Assembly)</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*b</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="left"><ptxt>Waveform</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Using an oscilloscope, check the signal waveform of the meter.</ptxt><table><title>Measurement Condition</title><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.07in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.06in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Item</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Content</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>L25-11 (S) - Body ground</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tool Setting</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>5 V/DIV., 10 msec./DIV.</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Engine idling</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><atten4><ptxt>As the coolant temperature rises, the period &quot;A&quot; shown in the illumination becomes longer.</ptxt></atten4><spec type="other"><title>OK</title><specitem><ptxt>The waveform displayed is as shown in the illustration.</ptxt></specitem></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-1"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-1"><actiontitle>REPLACE COMBINATION METER ASSEMBLY</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000GAVM"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="3-2" childid="RM100000000FSUV_01_0008"/></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FSUV_01_0008" cellposition="3-2"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (COMBINATION METER ASSEMBLY - ECM)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the L25 combination meter assembly connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the I84*1 or A29*2 ECM connector.</ptxt><list1 type="nonmark"><item><ptxt>*1: for LHD</ptxt><ptxt>*2: for RHD</ptxt></item></list1></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value (s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="resistance"><title>Standard Resistance</title><table><title>for LHD</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>L25-11 (S) - I84-12 (THWO)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>L25-11 (S) or I84-12 (THWO) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table><title>for RHD</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>L25-11 (S) - A29-12 (THWO)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><ro